This paper discusses neural network activation functions and their impact on training deep neural architectures on large and complex datasets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the visualization and understanding of self-modularization, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks for retrieval over large datasets, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
